            "title": "SPAIS",
            "children": [{
                "title": "Contemporary Feminist Thought",
                "children": [{
                    "title": "Description",
                    "text": "This unit not only requires students to think about academic theorists conceptualize gender and sex, but also how that is relevant to politics, citizenship and democracy."
                  },
                  {
                    "title": "Assessment",
                    "text": "\n\n - 25% - 'Feature Article' on a famous feminist. This can be a real or imagined publication and requires students to think about how the famous feminist would talk  but also develop their own interview style, and how that would fit the tone of their publication. \n - 75% - A briefing proposing a research programme to a 'think tank' that includes an action plan and budget. This demonstrates students using their skills to consider multiple stakeholders and how that could be relevant to the real world."
                  },
                  {
                    "title": "Learning",
                    "text": "This module requires students to think about how feminist thought is relevant to the 'real-world' in issues such as maternity leave and pay and discrimination.  They should acquire skills outside of the classroom such as budgeting and engaging non-academic writing."
                  }
